gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
WESTERN CAROLINA U. HERBARIUM
WCUH0031419

Flora of the Southern Appalachians

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.)
<Diapensiaceae>

Jackson County, NC. Shoulder of Whiteside mountain road between Cashiers and Highlands ¼ mile before trail/parking area.
Evergreen groundcover with glabrous leaves, dark green, shiny adaxial surface, glaucous and scaly abaxial.
Located in moist soil, dappled shade beneath *Betula lenta*.

35° 4' 54.1" N 83° 8' 31.1" W
elevation: 1330 m
7 February 2016                                                                     coll. Joey Borders #3


*Galax urceolata*
*Betula lenta*
